// pugutils_dp_new.rs
//
// Drop-in replacement for the DP quantification module.
// Function and struct names match exactly what quant.rs imports:
//
//   use crate::pugutils_dp_new::{get_num_molecules_log_dp_new, DpConfig};
//
// ── Changes from original pugutils_dp.rs ─────────────────────────────────
//  1. vertex_mean_loglik_for_named_txp() — new helper (mean_ll instead of sum_ll)
//  2. dp_best_subtree_for_tx()          — uses mean helper (one line changed)
//  3. get_num_molecules_log_dp_new()    — renamed (was get_num_molecules_log_dp)
//  4. Diagnostic counters               — gated behind DP_DIAG env var:
//       DP_DIAG=1 cargo run ...
//     prints per-run summary to stderr so you can see *why* results don't change.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// ── Three reasons results can be identical for all lambda/tau ─────────────
//
//  CAUSE A — Graph is all singletons (most common)
//    Every UMI has no edit-distance-1 neighbour in this dataset, so every
//    connected component has size 1.  The DP code never runs — the singleton
//    branch handles everything.  Lambda and tau are irrelevant.
//    Diagnosis: "multi_vertex_comps = 0" in the diagnostic output.
//
//  CAUSE B — probs_for_eq_umi_tx returns length-1 vectors (second most common)
//    The ProbMap stores one aggregated score per (eqid, umi_idx), not one
//    entry per raw read.  So n=1 always, mean_ll = sum_ll exactly, and the
//    mean fix does nothing.
//    Diagnosis: "max_prob_vec_len = 1" in the diagnostic output.
//
//  CAUSE C — tau gate blocks every child before the DP score matters
//    vertex_tx_delta uses sum_ll from vertex_loglik_for_tx, not mean_ll.
//    If tau is already filtering all children, varying lambda changes nothing
//    because no child ever reaches the absorption test.
//    Diagnosis: "total_children_tried = 0" alongside non-zero multi_vertex_comps.
//
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

